msgid "data/events_piracy.xml$//textList[@name=\"TEXT_ENCOUNTER_PIRATE\"]/text[1]"
msgstr ""
"As you jump into the system a pirate advances on your position. They are "
"refusing all hails. Prepare for a fight."

#: src-en/data/events_piracy.xml:115
msgid "data/events_piracy.xml$//textList[@name=\"TEXT_ENCOUNTER_PIRATE\"]/text[2]"
msgstr ""
"Soon after arriving in the system you are hailed by a small cruiser. \"What "
"good fortune that we happen to run into each other. Nothing personal, but "
"you have some information we need!\""

#: src-en/data/events_piracy.xml:116
msgid "data/events_piracy.xml$//textList[@name=\"TEXT_ENCOUNTER_PIRATE\"]/text[3]"
msgstr ""
"The only other ship at this beacon messages you: \"Finally, after months of "
"waiting, someone has fallen into our trap!\""

#: src-en/data/events_piracy.xml:117
msgid "data/events_piracy.xml$//textList[@name=\"TEXT_ENCOUNTER_PIRATE\"]/text[4]"
msgstr ""
"You barely have time to register jump completion before your ship warns you "
"of an incoming ship with weapons hot."

#: src-en/data/events_piracy.xml:124
msgid "data/events_piracy.xml$//event[@name=\"ENCOUNTER_MERCENARY\"]/choice/text"
msgstr "Continue..."

#: src-en/data/events_piracy.xml:129
msgid ""
"data/events_piracy.xml$//textList[@name=\"TEXT_ENCOUNTER_MERCENARY\"]/text[1]"
msgstr ""
"You spot a small black market at this beacon, but as you approach it a "
"mercenary ship swings around and attacks. \"Hah! What luck of ours. Our "
"clients came here to hire us to scout you out, and here you are in the very "
"same sector!\""

#: src-en/data/events_piracy.xml:130
msgid ""
"data/events_piracy.xml$//textList[@name=\"TEXT_ENCOUNTER_MERCENARY\"]/text[2]"
msgstr ""
"\"Wouldn't you know it, it's the captain of the hour! I assure you, it's "
"nothing personal. Just, we've been given quite a sum in return for your "
"head. You're a Renegade, so I'm sure you understand.\""

#: src-en/data/events_piracy.xml:131
msgid ""
"data/events_piracy.xml$//textList[@name=\"TEXT_ENCOUNTER_MERCENARY\"]/text[3]"
msgstr ""
"Seems someone's put a price on your head, because a mercenary is trailing "
"you, weapons online! No surprise, but seems you'll have to take care of this"
" first."

#: src-en/data/events_piracy.xml:132
msgid ""
"data/events_piracy.xml$//textList[@name=\"TEXT_ENCOUNTER_MERCENARY\"]/text[4]"
msgstr ""
"Strangely, Renegades and Mercenaries rarely get along. To the mercs, "
"Renegades lack the honor and distinction the Syndicate brings them. The "
"nearby ship seems to have taken that difference personally and lunges "
"towards you!"

#: src-en/data/events_piracy.xml:139
msgid "data/events_piracy.xml$//event[@name=\"ENCOUNTER_SMUGGLER\"]/choice/text"
msgstr "Continue..."

#: src-en/data/events_piracy.xml:144
msgid ""
"data/events_piracy.xml$//textList[@name=\"TEXT_ENCOUNTER_SMUGGLER\"]/text[1]"
msgstr ""
"\"I spy with my little eye a ship with some fine gear I'm sure will sell for"
" a pretty penny on the market! Surrender yourselves or suffer the wrath of "
"my cannons!\""

#: src-en/data/events_piracy.xml:145
msgid ""
"data/events_piracy.xml$//textList[@name=\"TEXT_ENCOUNTER_SMUGGLER\"]/text[2]"
msgstr ""
"Smugglers rarely show aggression for fear of losing their precious cargo. "
"Yet - when their stock is dry, sometimes the odd captain will try their luck"
" and seize the cargo of a passing ship. Seems a bit risky to pick on a ship "
"like yours, but that's their mistake."

#: src-en/data/events_piracy.xml:146
msgid ""
"data/events_piracy.xml$//textList[@name=\"TEXT_ENCOUNTER_SMUGGLER\"]/text[3]"
msgstr ""
"\"How quaint. I just sold off all my stock and here I was thinking I'd have "
"to make my trek back to Argeonn when you showed up! Thank you kindly for the"
" generous donation, stranger!\" You aren't sure what the smugglers are "
"referring to until weapons pop out of their hull!"

#: src-en/data/events_piracy.xml:147
msgid ""
"data/events_piracy.xml$//textList[@name=\"TEXT_ENCOUNTER_SMUGGLER\"]/text[4]"
msgstr ""
"A smuggler approaches, clearly intending to steal rather than to sell. "
"Prepare for combat!"

